OL,6,F"They heard us speaking in another
OL,7,Flanguage.
OL,9,F"They threw stones at our car and in
OL,10,Fmy garden, where my little child was
OL,11,Fplaying.
OL,13,F"The situation became very dangerous,
OL,14,Fand the group became more and more
OL,15,Faggressive.
OL,17,F"Even when I tried to talk to these
OL,18,Fkids they became even more aggressive.
OL,19,FThey stood in a group with sticks in
OL,20,Ftheir hands. They were shouting racial
OL,21,Fslurs.
